# UI test plan maintenance

Canonical catalog: `docs/UI_TEST_PLAN.md`.

## When you MUST update it (end of the same task)

Update the file before finishing if your changes affect anything a user can see or do:

- New or removed route, tab, modal, drawer, gate, or primary CTA
- New user workflow (create / edit / join / leave / chat / buy / bid / etc.)
- Changed expected behavior, validation, permissions, or empty/error states
- New filter, setting, overlay (`?player=`, `?item=`), or URL query sync
- New entity type, sport flow, or cross-cutting concern (offline, push, ads)

## When you may skip

- Refactor with no user-visible behavior change
- Backend-only change with no Frontend UX impact
- Typo/copy-only tweaks that do not change flow or outcomes
- User explicitly asked not to touch the test plan this task

## How to add entries

1. Place tests in the matching section (§4–§18); add a subsection only if the area is new.
2. Use the existing table format: `ID | Test | Steps | Expected` (or `ID | Test | Expected` for cross-cutting).
3. IDs: reuse section prefix (`G-`, `F-`, `GD-`, `CH-`, `PR-`, `X-`, etc.); next free number in that section.
4. For new matrices or personas, extend §3 or §19 — do not duplicate P0 lists unless priority truly changed.
5. Keep each row one testable outcome; split multi-step journeys into separate IDs.

## Minimum bar per change type

| Change | Add at least |
|--------|----------------|
| New screen/route | 1 happy-path + 1 access/empty or error case |
| New modal/form | 1 submit success + 1 validation or cancel |
| Changed behavior | Update or replace affected row(s); add regression row if old behavior could break |
| New workflow | Happy path + one permission or edge case |

Do not leave the test plan stale when the delivered feature has no row describing how to verify it in the UI.
